<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Words Ending With -AL</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">Word of the Day · 2-letter words</p>

<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The -AL suffix is Scrabble's workhorse ending. It converts nouns to adjectives (tropical, musical, logical) and appears in over 800 valid words. At just 2 tiles (A+L), it's the cheapest suffix to add — meaning you can extend board words without burning through your rack.</p>

<p>With 800+ options available, -AL gives you more flexibility than almost any other suffix when building from limited rack tiles.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why -AL Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
